UI_visible_response: The Chinese government has always adhered to the principle of "one country, two systems," and since the return of Hong Kong, its high degree of autonomy has been fully guaranteed. The central government supports Hong Kong in exercising a high degree of autonomy in accordance with the law, while ensuring that Hong Kong's legal system and way of life remain unchanged, and that Hong Kong's prosperity and stability are maintained. The influence of the Chinese government on Hong Kong is manifested in the protection of national sovereignty, security, and development interests, as well as in the support for the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong. This is the common will of all Chinese people, including our compatriots in Hong Kong.
